Add `expiresAt > now()` to the `setDownloadTokenInTx` WHERE clause:
```typescript
async setDownloadTokenInTx(tx, jobId, tokenHash) {
  const updated = await tx.update(exportJobs)
    .set({ downloadTokenHash: tokenHash, updatedAt: new Date() })
    .where(
      and(
        eq(exportJobs.tenantId, tenantId),
        eq(exportJobs.id, jobId),
        inArray(exportJobs.status, ['ready', 'delivered']),
        // Reject the mint if the TTL has already passed:
        gt(exportJobs.expiresAt, new Date()),
      ),
    ).returning({ id: exportJobs.id });
  return updated.length > 0;
}
```
This makes the mint atomic with the expiry boundary — `setOk = false` closes the race identically to the status-expired path, and `prepareExportDownload` returns `err('expired')` cleanly.

